WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
The Bible reading this morning is taken from John's Gospel, chapter 14 verses 1 to 7.

2
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:21.000
Let not your hearts be troubled. Believe in God. Believe also in me.

3
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
In my Father's house are many rooms.

4
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.000
If it were not so, would I have told you that I go to prepare a place for you?

5
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:38.000
And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again and will take you to myself,

6
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:46.000
that where I am, you may be also. And you know the way to where I am going.

7
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:54.000
Thomas said to him, Lord, we do not know where you are going. How can we know the way?

8
00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:06.000
Jesus said to him, I am the way and the truth and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me.

9
00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:16.000
If you had known me, you would have known my Father also. From now on, you do know him and have seen him.

10
00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:18.000
This is the word of the Lord.

11
00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:27.000
Amen, let's pray together.

12
00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:39.000
Lord, as we read a moment ago in Psalm 25, we prayed the same again.

13
00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.000
We prayed, Lord, make known your ways to us. Teach us your paths.

14
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:51.000
Lead us in your truth and teach us for you are the God of our salvation.

15
00:01:51.000 --> 00:02:00.000
And so we're looking at John chapter 14 this morning. This is the sixth of the I am statements that we're working through.

16
00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:07.000
There are seven total in the gospel of John. We have the seventh in John 14, six.

17
00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:13.000
When I was little, one of my favorite places to go was Nanny and Popol's house.

18
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:16.000
They lived just down the road from where we're sat here.

19
00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:22.000
And I always remember just getting there. The door was never locked and so we just let ourselves in.

20
00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:26.000
And every time I would go in, the first place I would go to would be the Popol's lazy boy.

21
00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.000
And he would be sat there. He would almost never get up.

22
00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.000
But he was always there and he was ready for a hug. We would kind of dive on him and give him a hug.

23
00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:39.000
It was always wonderful to be greeted by him and to feel at home there.

24
00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:45.000
But always there beside his lazy boy was a little wooden table.

25
00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:52.000
And he always had a cup of coffee or a cup that had had coffee in it, the remote control and his Bible.

26
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:59.000
But there was one day when he got up from his lazy boy for the last time.

27
00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.000
And nobody knew that that would be the case and he didn't know it either.

28
00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:14.000
And when people went back to the house, I wasn't there, but they went back and they found that sure enough his Bible was there beside his chair.

29
00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:18.000
And it was opened up to John chapter 14.

30
00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:26.000
And what a wonderful passage of Scripture to read on your final day on earth, John chapter 14.

31
00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:31.000
It's a comfort to me to think that these were the very words that he was reading on that day.

32
00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:37.000
Because what Jesus says here gives us hope both in life, but also in death.

33
00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:42.000
It gives us comfort for ourselves knowing where we are going, if our trust is in Jesus.

34
00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:47.000
But also comfort for those that we love who know him as well.

35
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:53.000
Here Jesus shows us the way to our eternal home.

36
00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:58.000
He does so by saying several different things here.

37
00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:01.000
We're just going to kind of lock into three aspects.

38
00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:05.000
We're going to see the problem that he and the disciples are facing.

39
00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:07.000
And then we're going to see the place that he is going.

40
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:09.000
And then last of all, we're going to see the path to get there.

41
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:14.000
But let's just see the problem of what is going on here just to set the scene.

42
00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:20.000
This is a very difficult time for Jesus and for his disciples.

43
00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:25.000
Last week, we were looking at the very public raising of Lazarus.

44
00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:32.000
And we mentioned that right after that, we see that that is the very thing that sets the plan to put Jesus to death in motion.

45
00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:34.000
Alright, so this is a very public thing.

46
00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:36.000
People are already looking to put him to death.

47
00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.000
But now that many people have seen this and they believe they want to put Jesus to death.

48
00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:43.000
The religious authorities do anyway.

49
00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:51.000
So you've got this possibility of death looming over their heads.

50
00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:53.000
And the disciples are really feeling this.

51
00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:58.000
And so you have this kind of external problem, if you will, that's looming.

52
00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:04.000
So they know that the hour of death has come for Jesus, that that is near.

53
00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:06.000
They know that they are in danger as well.

54
00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.000
And so Jesus knows that this is coming to him.

55
00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:15.000
But here what we see is it's not so much a problem as it is God's purpose being fulfilled.

56
00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.000
This is the very purpose for which Jesus came to die on the cross.

57
00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:25.000
And so you read in John chapter 12 verses 27 and 28, Jesus prays, he says this.

58
00:05:26.000 --> 00:05:28.000
He says, now is my soul troubled.

59
00:05:29.000 --> 00:05:30.000
And what shall I say?

60
00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:32.000
Father, save me from this hour.

61
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:37.000
But for this purpose I have come to this hour.

62
00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:41.000
Father, glorify your name.

63
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:46.000
So Jesus knows that he's come for this purpose, for this very hour.

64
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:48.000
The hour of his death.

65
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.000
And the glory that God will receive through it.

66
00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
So Jesus then gathers his disciples after praying this.

67
00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
And he speaks to them in private in what has come to be known as the farewell discourse.

68
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:06.000
If you have a Bible open in front of you and you've got words in red, you'll see words in red over the next few chapters.

69
00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:10.000
As Jesus is gathering his disciples to speak to them for this final time.

70
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:12.000
It's night time.

71
00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
They know that Jesus' life is under threat and Jesus then tells them near the start.

72
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:21.000
He tells them that one of them is going to betray or, yeah, one of them is going to betray Jesus.

73
00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:24.000
Of course we then know that that is Judas.

74
00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:30.000
And then after he says that one of them is going to betray him, then you've then got Peter talking about how he's never going to deny Jesus.

75
00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:34.000
And Jesus says this very night, you are going to deny me.

76
00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:37.000
So these are really troubling times here.

77
00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:41.000
But it's not just about the external trouble that is happening.

78
00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:46.000
It's also about the internal kind of trouble that is going on in the disciples, the turmoil they are facing.

79
00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:49.000
As they're hearing that somebody is about to betray Jesus.

80
00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:53.000
Peter says he's willing to lay down his life for Jesus, but Jesus says you're going to deny him.

81
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:57.000
So they feel the kind of darkness surrounding them.

82
00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:00.000
And yet Jesus says in verse one of chapter 14,

83
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:05.000
Let not your hearts be troubled.

84
00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:10.000
Where troubled conveys the idea of a kind of strong inner turmoil.

85
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:14.000
That's what they're feeling in the midst of these difficult circumstances.

86
00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:21.000
But you can imagine them hearing Jesus say this after all he's just said about betrayal and denial to then say let not your hearts be troubled.

87
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:29.000
I mean, not to trivialize this at all, but I can't help but think about, you know, buzz saying to Woody,

88
00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:36.000
Now, Woody, this is no time to panic. And Woody answers, this is a perfect time to panic.

89
00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:38.000
You know, so Jesus is saying don't be troubled.

90
00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:41.000
The disciples are like, what do you mean, don't be troubled?

91
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:46.000
How could Jesus possibly say this facing death?

92
00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:50.000
You know, these disciples have left behind everything to follow Jesus.

93
00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:53.000
Now it seems like all of that is going to be for nothing.

94
00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.000
And they may very well lose their lives because of this too.

95
00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:00.000
How could Jesus say don't be troubled?

96
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:11.000
This is not a kind of grandiose statement that dismisses their concerns or is detached from reality or the reality of the difficulties they are facing.

97
00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:20.000
Because the very word he uses to speak to his disciples here when he says, let not your hearts be troubled was what he said in his prayer a moment ago.

98
00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.000
That's why I read it in chapter 12 verse 27.

99
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:26.000
He says, Father, my soul is troubled.

100
00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:28.000
So he's experiencing this trouble.

101
00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:33.000
And the inner turmoil wasn't like forever gone once he had prayed.

102
00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:35.000
It returns again.

103
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:43.000
So when Jesus begins this kind of final discourse in chapter 13 verse 21, we're told that he was troubled in spirit.

104
00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:54.000
So what we have here is this troubled man Jesus saying to his troubled disciples, let not your hearts be troubled.

105
00:08:55.000 --> 00:09:03.000
So here we see that Jesus knows exactly how they are feeling and more when he says this to them.

106
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:09.000
And yet in his time of greatest need, his thought is for his disciples.

107
00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:11.000
He is taking care of them.

108
00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:13.000
And the same is true of us.

109
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:16.000
When he says to us, don't let your hearts be troubled.

110
00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:22.000
This is somebody who knows exactly what it is to suffer like we suffer and even more.

111
00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:30.000
And this is him speaking to us from a place of genuine care, knowing what we need.

112
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.000
He knows what it's like to experience turmoil, trouble.

113
00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.000
And yet he says, don't be troubled.

114
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:39.000
He gives the flip side of being troubled.

115
00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:41.000
He says, believe in God.

116
00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.000
Believe also in me.

117
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
He isn't saying believe God exists and your troubles will go away.

118
00:09:49.000 --> 00:10:00.000
He's telling the disciples that in the midst of their fear, they can still put their faith in God and hold on to him and what he has promised.

119
00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:04.000
In the midst of their fear, he calls them to faith.

120
00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:06.000
So they know that they're to believe God.

121
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:10.000
But notice what he says after that, believe in God, believe also in me.

122
00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:13.000
So what is Jesus telling us about himself there?

123
00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:16.000
He's saying that he is as trustworthy as the Father.

124
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:21.000
They can trust in his word as the very word of God.

125
00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:23.000
Why?

126
00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:26.000
Because he is, as we've been seeing, the I am.

127
00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:30.000
So in the midst of trouble and uncertainty, he is the constant.

128
00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:32.000
He is the certainty.

129
00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:38.000
The hope in the midst of turmoil is found by trusting in him.

130
00:10:39.000 --> 00:10:47.000
So when we are faced with uncertainty, even the uncertainty of death, we can place our hope in the certainty of his promises.

131
00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.000
Now they may or may not disappear immediately the troubles that we're facing.

132
00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
But Jesus is pointing us to where our hope is found and it is found in him.

133
00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:02.000
Alright, so Jesus then takes this general statement about their trouble and trusting in God, this problem that they're facing.

134
00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:05.000
But then he applies it specifically to death.

135
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:09.000
Because that is what they are facing specifically here.

136
00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:12.000
What he says gives us hope in the face of death.

137
00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:15.000
He talks about the place where he's going.

138
00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
This is where, this is the truth he wants them to believe about the place he's going.

139
00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.000
He says, believe also in me, verse 2,

140
00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:28.000
In my father's house are many rooms.

141
00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:33.000
If it were not so, what I've told you that I go to prepare a place for you.

142
00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:36.000
So Jesus tells them he's going to his father's house.

143
00:11:37.000 --> 00:11:39.000
He's going to prepare a place for them.

144
00:11:41.000 --> 00:11:47.000
If you grew up in church, you'll probably heard and sung songs based on this very verse.

145
00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:51.000
I grew up in, once a couple different churches, but one was pretty traditional.

146
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:56.000
And so we would open up our hymn books and we would sing, I've got a mansion just over the hilltop.

147
00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:58.000
Does anybody know that song?

148
00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:02.000
And we would sing about the mansion that was based on a translation, the King James version of this.

149
00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:09.000
Where it says in my father's house are many mansions, but that word doesn't mean kind of how we think of it now.

150
00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:12.000
So it was confusing and we all thought we were going to get a mansion one day.

151
00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:16.000
It's going to be great, but it may not be exactly as we thought in that song.

152
00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:22.000
But then things got cleared up when I went to a youth group and we sang the classic Theologically Sounds.

153
00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:25.000
Big house by Audio Adrenaline.

154
00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.000
Common Go With Me to My Father's House.

155
00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:30.000
Do you remember how it was described?

156
00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:32.000
It's a big, big house with lots and lots of room.

157
00:12:33.000 --> 00:12:34.000
It's a big, big table with lots and lots of food.

158
00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:36.000
A big, big yard where we can play football.

159
00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:38.000
It's a big house.

160
00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.000
It's my father's house.

161
00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:42.000
This is the word of the Lord.

162
00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:50.000
If you gather around my bedside and I'm dying, it'd be wonderful to have a song or two, but please don't sing that song.

163
00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:58.000
So there's a lot of ideas floating around, speculation about what heaven is like.

164
00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:05.000
But it is important to see what scripture teaches and stick with that.

165
00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:07.000
And what it emphasizes as well.

166
00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:09.000
So where is Jesus going?

167
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:11.000
He's going to the Father's house.

168
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:20.000
So the focal point though of what Jesus is saying here is not what the house is like, but whose house it is.

169
00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:22.000
He's going to the house of the Father.

170
00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:28.000
And he's using the imagery of a house to speak of God's dwelling place.

171
00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:35.000
So he's speaking of dwelling in God's presence and finding our home in Him.

172
00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:39.000
This is where Jesus is heading to the presence of his Father.

173
00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:44.000
And God's house or his dwelling is a theme that stretches right the way throughout scripture.

174
00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:50.000
So Adam and Eve are dwelling with God in the cool of the garden.

175
00:13:51.000 --> 00:14:01.000
You've got 2 Samuel 7 and verse 13 where God says that David's offspring is going to build a house for my name.

176
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:08.000
See this being fulfilled initially in the temple that is built where God's presence is made known among his people.

177
00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:13.000
But that was ultimately pointing to the coming of Jesus and him building his church.

178
00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:22.000
So in 2 Corinthians chapter 6 verse 16 we the church are referred to as the temple of the living God, the Lord's house.

179
00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.000
He makes his dwelling in us as his people.

180
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:34.000
And then in John chapter 14 and verse 23 Jesus speaks in that way about God making his home with us.

181
00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:39.000
So chapter 14 verse 23 if you've got a Bible with you have a look at that verse.

182
00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:44.000
Jesus speaks about the Father, he and the Father making their home with us.

183
00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:48.000
They're taking up residence in the lives of those who love him.

184
00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:50.000
How does this happen?

185
00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:54.000
It happens when the Holy Spirit comes and takes up residence in us.

186
00:14:55.000 --> 00:15:01.000
So there's a very real sense in which we the church are the Father's house where he makes up his home with us.

187
00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:08.000
But at the same time at the start of the chapter that's not what it's saying.

188
00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:17.000
So yes God takes up residence in us but in the start of the chapter this is not a place for God to dwell.

189
00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:21.000
It's a place for us to dwell in the Father's house.

190
00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:24.000
So this is the people of God being welcomed into the presence of God.

191
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:29.000
It is us going to our heavenly home where there are many rooms.

192
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:33.000
There's room for everyone who puts their faith in Christ all over the world.

193
00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:41.000
If you dwell or rather if he dwells in you you will dwell with him.

194
00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:43.000
This is what is being taught here.

195
00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:45.000
So we're dwelling in the presence of God.

196
00:15:46.000 --> 00:15:47.000
So when will that happen?

197
00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:51.000
When will we dwell in the presence of God?

198
00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:54.000
When will we go to the Father's house to be with him?

199
00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:56.000
Forever.

200
00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:58.000
Is it when we die?

201
00:15:59.000 --> 00:16:02.000
Or is it when Jesus comes again?

202
00:16:03.000 --> 00:16:04.000
What does Scripture teach?

203
00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:11.000
We touched on this in passing last week but I thought it would be good for us to slow down a little bit this week and see what Scripture says about this.

204
00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:14.000
So what happens when a believer dies?

205
00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:16.000
Well two things.

206
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:22.000
One is there's what theologians tend to refer to as the intermediate state.

207
00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:24.000
The intermediate state.

208
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:26.000
What do I mean by that?

209
00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:28.000
I don't mean purgatory.

210
00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:30.000
That's not what Scripture teaches.

211
00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:40.000
What Scripture teaches is that when we die physically, spiritually we go to be with the Lord.

212
00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:46.000
And it's that state of spiritually being with the Lord that is that kind of intermediate state being with the Lord spiritually.

213
00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:49.000
So what are some examples of this in Scripture?

214
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:51.000
So Luke 23 verse 43.

215
00:16:52.000 --> 00:16:53.000
You've got the thief next to Jesus on the cross.

216
00:16:54.000 --> 00:17:00.000
Jesus says, truly truly I say to you today you will be with me in paradise.

217
00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:04.000
So that very day when he dies, the thief was going to be with him in paradise.

218
00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:06.000
Though his body died, his spirit will be with the Lord.

219
00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:10.000
Second Corinthians chapter 5 verses 6 to 8.

220
00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:17.000
There we see that the language of home is being used to describe leaving our physical bodies and going to be with the Lord.

221
